CONCLUSION: Atlantic South-westerlies and Tropical-Plumes are the major drivers of rainfall

Across 8–13 April 2025, the TCWV maps show a large reservoir of moisture over the tropical Sahel and a growing moist band over the eastern Atlantic west of Morocco. 
The VIMF fields then show a strong south-west to north-east moisture transport corridor extending from the subtropical Atlantic into Morocco and western Algeria.
The VIMC maps confirm that these flows converge over Morocco during 9–11 April, where moisture accumulates near the study site.
